<subsection xml:id="subsec-area-of-a-part-of-a-circle-in-real-life" xmlns:xi="http://www.w3.org/2001/XInclude">
    <title>Area of a Part of a Circle in Real-Life</title>
    <objectives component="outcomes">
        <introduction xml:id="auto_dfai3eme">
            <p xml:id="auto_2r6kuv02">
            <dl>
                <li xml:id="auto_by3awu32">
                    <title>Strand</title>
                    <p xml:id="auto_ej2n2vk6">
                        2.0 Measurements and Geometry
                    </p>
                </li>
                <li xml:id="auto_u7irad7e">
                    <title>Sub-Strand</title>
                    <p xml:id="auto_pcm6n66f">
                        2.6 Area of a Part of a Circle
                    </p>
                </li>
                <li xml:id="auto_lvswbb3o">
                    <title>Specific Learning Outcomes</title>
                    <p xml:id="auto_itfdw4zc">
                        Apply formulas for sectors, segments, and annuli to solve real-life problems involving pizza slicing, washers, and signal coverage.
                    </p>
                </li>
                <li xml:id="auto_c1nfms19" component="lesson-plan">
                    <title>Grade Level</title>
                    <p xml:id="auto_ks751uao">
                        10
                    </p>
                </li>
                <li xml:id="auto_icnihism" component="lesson-plan">
                    <title>Estimated Duration</title>
                    <p xml:id="auto_d25quyxh">
                        40 minutes
                    </p>
                </li>
            </dl>
            </p>
            <p xml:id="auto_2i48cc04" component="lesson-plan">
                <p xml:id="auto_xj8xqg5r"> Upon completion of this lesson, learners will be able to:
                <ol>
                    <li xml:id="auto_r6qhedeu">
                        <p xml:id="auto_qfjuc0up">
                            <alert>Know (Conceptual Understanding):</alert> Understand that area of a part of a circle refers to calculating the area of sectors, segments, or annuli. Identify real-life contexts where each shape occurs (pizza slices, washers, signal overlap).
                        </p>
                    </li>
                    <li xml:id="auto_jlaq1g9p">
                        <p xml:id="auto_0rqk6724">
                            <alert>Do (Procedural Skill):</alert> Apply the correct formula for sectors (<m>A = \frac{\theta}{360} \times \pi r^2</m>), annuli (<m>A = \pi(R^2 - r^2)</m>), and segments (<m>A = A_{\text{sector}} - A_{\text{triangle}}</m>) to calculate areas.
                        </p>
                    </li>
                    <li xml:id="auto_uzokjx48">
                        <p xml:id="auto_cpt9la15">
                            <alert>Apply (Application/Problem-Solving):</alert> Solve real-world problems involving pizza slicing, metal washers, signal coverage overlap, garden paths, and other practical applications.
                        </p>
                    </li>
                </ol>
                </p>
            </p>
        </introduction>
    </objectives>
    <axiom component="resources">
        <!-- Link to blurb -->
        <xi:include href="../../resources-blurb-lesson.ptx" />

        <sbsgroup widths="45% 45%" margins="2% 2%">
            <sidebyside>
                <p xml:id="auto_rk1fogex">
                    <dataurl source="lesson_plans/measurements-and-geometry/area-of-a-part-of-a-circle/area-of-a-part-of-a-circle-in-real-life.pdf"> Lesson Plan </dataurl>
                </p>
                <p xml:id="auto_b2l43cw1">
                    <dataurl source="lesson_plans/measurements-and-geometry/area-of-a-part-of-a-circle/step-by-step-guide_area-of-a-part-of-a-circle-in-real-life.pdf"> Step-by-Step Guide </dataurl>
                </p>
            </sidebyside>
        </sbsgroup>
    </axiom>
